@JHadden123

you can find some examples / explanations here : [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grid_fin](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grid_fin) ![:)](//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif)

basically, a grid fin, like a tail fin, is a control surface used to steer / stabilize an aircraft (generally used in missiles / rockets) in atmosphere. however, contrary to classic tail fins, they can be easily folded against the body of the vehicle, allowing compact storage.

instead of having a big vertical surface, you have a lot of small surfaces in a grid pattern ![:)](//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif)

